learning_outcomes.en:
Learning outcomes:
- knows the key terms and process of research work, and the types and forms of research work. Can select a research topic and set a goal for it;
- can plan research work, knows how to find professional literature and can use databases, can critically evaluate research work and reference sources;
- is aware of the requirements on the subject of research, can formulate the subject, can pose research tasks and hypotheses, can systematically treat the matter, knows the process of constructing and using a model;
- has acquired the skills of referencing and citing; can prepare a correct bibliography of literature and sources; can independently analyse text structure and prepare and formalise a table of contents; 
- has experience in formulating conclusions and suggestions on the basis of processed source data;
- knows the principles of research ethics and can use them;
- knows the main rules and requirements for formalising research work and can independently formalise conducted research into a comprehensive paper: title page, table of contents, introduction, the body text with necessary divisions (theory, methods, conditions, and results of conducting research) and illustrative material, conclusion, references, annexes - all formalised in accordance with the University of Tartu Narva College's guidelines for written student papers and other rules applied;
- as a result of the course, the student has improved his/her style of writing and acquired the skills of using a scientific style.

learning_outcomes.et:
Üliõpilane: 

- kavandab uurimistöö; 

- valib ja kasutab töö eesmärgist lähtuvalt sobivaid uurimismeetodeid; 

- hindab kriitiliselt uurimusi ja andmeallikaid; 

- järgib teadustööle esitatavaid sisulisi, vormistuslikke ja eetilisi nõudeid;
